n","ttype":"human","tale":"Fur Pen ia a human settlement that worships Astennu, a baboon god associated with Thoth. They identify with Thoth mainly in his aspect as a god of writing.\r\nThe fairly large settlement was founded originally by worshipers of Thoth himself. They are famous for having a library of their own which is independent of the great Bibliotec in Gyptia. Also, because they saved a small band of baboons from the ravages of The Transit, they gradually have come to worship Astennu. He has become their most direct patron. They are said to be working on uplifts.\r\nThe residents are more interested in making discoveries from the dark lands to their west than trading, but they do sometimes have valuable material to trade with others. They are an adaptable and tolerant group because, besides being near the edge of the habitable zone, the area is multi-cultural (many dwarf, elf, and gnoll settlers) and the settlement is all about learning. A petrified book which is impossible to read and is said to have been the first creation of Astennu is nearby and provides focus for the settlement and its residents.","fertility":1280,"lvl":-150,"s":"snb"},"a002193":{"xpos":2,"ypos":193,"k":"a002193","fertility":20,"lvl":-1,"s":"sNEWABcd"},"a002194":{"xpos":2,"ypos":194,"k":"a002194","fertility":10,"lvl":0,"s":"sNAB"},"a002195":{"xpos":2,"ypos":195,"k":"a002195","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"NEWABCD"},"a002196":{"xpos":2,"ypos":196,"k":"a002196","fertility":80,"lvl":2,"s":"EWABCD"},"a002197":{"xpos":2,"ypos":197,"k":"a002197","fertility":160,"lvl":2,"s":"SEWABCD"},"a002198":{"xpos":2,"ypos":198,"k":"a002198","fertility":10,"lvl":1,"s":"SnEWABcd"},"a002199":{"xpos":2,"ypos":199,"k":"a002199","fertility":80,"lvl":0,"s":"new"},"a003000":{"xpos":3,"ypos":0,"k":"a003000","fertility":20,"lvl":10,"s":""},"a003001":{"xpos":3,"ypos":1,"k":"a003001","fertility":40,"lvl":10,"s":""},"a003002":{"xpos":3,"ypos":2,"k":"a003002","fertility":10,"lvl":10,"s":""},"a003003":{"xpos":3,"ypos":3