s is Good Enough\". We would love to know more.","fertility":1280,"lvl":-300,"s":"EaBd"},"a007190":{"xpos":7,"ypos":190,"k":"a007190","fertility":10,"lvl":-300,"s":"wB"},"a007191":{"xpos":7,"ypos":191,"k":"a007191","fertility":10,"lvl":-300,"s":"sacd"},"a007192":{"xpos":7,"ypos":192,"k":"a007192","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":"sNABcd"},"a007193":{"xpos":7,"ypos":193,"k":"a007193","fertility":80,"lvl":-1,"s":"sNABcd"},"a007194":{"xpos":7,"ypos":194,"k":"a007194","tname":"Mehet-Weret","ttype":"human","tale":"Mehet-Weret is a human settlement founded by descendants of farmers and herders who dwelt near Gyptia before The Transit. Perhaps they understood and even shared other people's disillusionment with Alphito after that event. Even so, they could not abandon their attachment to the earth. They revived the cult of a minor goddess named Mehet-Weret (a celestial cow goddess), named their settlement after her, and adapted her to new animals being raised in the new, desolate, Alphito. These are greatly modified versions of the animals they used to raise.\r\n The settlers trade with nearby villages and sometimes even brave the trail to Gyptia with their cattle herds. The horde respects them quite a bit because their attachment to their herds echoes horde culture. However, the land nearby is not well adapted even to herding these animals. People from the village often need to graze them far from home (as the horde do) and are often challenged.\r\nThey are said to support a small camp to The Wild Way which is dedicated to finding creatures to uplift or adapt for herding in this desolate land.","fertility":320,"lvl":0,"s":"sNABcd"},"a007195":{"xpos":7,"ypos":195,"k":"a007195","fertility":80,"lvl":2,"s":"NAB"},"a007196":{"xpos":7,"ypos":196,"k":"a007196","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"sd"},"a007197":{"xpos":7,"ypos":197,"k":"a007197","fertility":10,"lvl":150,"s":"NEAB"},"a007198":{"xpos":7,"ypos":198,"k":"a007198","fertility":20,"lvl":150,"s":"sB"},"a007199":{"xpos":7,"ypos":199,"k":"a007199","tname":"Climbers Paradise","ttype":"uplift","tale":"Climber's Paradise is another uplift. What was uplifted? This is an area that is mountainous, 1800 feet above the old sea level and near to some very hot terrain. The uplifted creatures were originally giant goats. They have become a mountainous version of centaur, much like the uplifted seahorses from Swift Thought, only more so. These creatures always study more than one of the twelve ways after they mature. The main study is never a dedicated spell caster or dedicated sneak. The way of rage is a popular way of study.\r\nThe closest settlements are the Quick Forge dwarfs, and the huge down-lifted Hesat community that worships a defective cow goddess. The borderlands human and elf communities who venture often into darkness are also in range. Exploring the hot heights in the uninhabitable lands is \"a thing\" for this group. Otherwise, just staying alive is the goal.They worship Ba-ảakhu-hā-f. This is a ram headed god otherwise ? to us. They have built an elaborate shrine to him.","fertility":640,"lvl":300,"s":"NEWAB"},"a008000":{"xpos":8,"ypos":0,"k":"a008000","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":"wd"},"a008001":{"xpos":8,"ypos":1,"k":"a008001","tname":"Happy Sprook","ttype":"human","tstory":"Happy Sprook was founded in the year 445 PT, in the month of Second Peragni, by members of Windsail Family from Gyptia. Now, Windsail Family and its rival, Umberfroth and Associates , vie for rule of Happy Sprook. Control of the town changes frequently and violently. The town's health depends on Choke Berry found there. Happy Sprook is currently challenged by unknown raiders. ","fertility":640,"lvl":2,"s":"wad"},"a008002":{"xpos":8,"ypos":2,"k":"a008002","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"wad"},"a008003":{"xpos":8,"ypos":3,"k":"a008003","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":"wa"},"a008004":{"xpos":8,"ypos":4,"k":"a008004","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":"a"},"a008005":{"xpos":8,"ypos":5,"k":"a008005","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a008006":{