:-150,"s":""},"a017163":{"xpos":17,"ypos":163,"k":"a017163","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":""},"a017164":{"xpos":17,"ypos":164,"k":"a017164","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":""},"a017165":{"xpos":17,"ypos":165,"k":"a017165","fertility":80,"lvl":-150,"s":"D"},"a017166":{"xpos":17,"ypos":166,"k":"a017166","fertility":40,"lvl":-150,"s":"SWCD"},"a017167":{"xpos":17,"ypos":167,"k":"a017167","fertility":10,"lvl":-300,"s":"nbC"},"a017168":{"xpos":17,"ypos":168,"k":"a017168","fertility":40,"lvl":-300,"s":"Ed"},"a017169":{"xpos":17,"ypos":169,"k":"a017169","tname":"Swift Thought","ttype":"uplift","tale":"Swift Thought is an uplift settlement. Originally, its land was 300 fathoms below The Mid-Earth Sea. So what was uplifted first lived below the sea, namely, a herd of Giant Sea Horse. They never dwelt 300 fathoms down. Creatures from that depth would be strange indeed. Those depths of the Mid-Earth Sea were actually sterile in any case. These creatures were always roving, and homeless. They have become a type of desert dwelling centaur - head of a horse, body of a camel, arms like a humanoid. What are their goals now?\r\nThere are 3 known factions, a simple trichotomy. One faction wants to get along with The Horde, one faction wants to get along with the Gnolls and a balancing faction that wants to get along with both; or pit the horde against the gnolls and so maintain the independence of Swift Thought. The last faction is the one that usually holds power. Once they mature, these creatures always study more than one of the twelve ways. The main study is never fully devoted to spell casting or sneakiness.\r\nNames. Two qualities combined: King of the Swift; Prince of Brawn. Or vice versa: Swift King, Strong Prince. Typical qualities involve Social Station (Nobility, Trade), Physical Virtue, (less often) Mental or Spiritual Virtue, (less often still) Contemplative or Aesthetic Virtue. There are still other less prestigious qualities or attributes that are sometimes used as names (like Short Hair, Long Legs, Limper, Loquacious).\r\nBesides curiosity, there are few known reasons for adventurers to travel here. There is always some tension among the horde, the gnolls, and these uplifted ones. A group of adventurers might upset the balance in these. And, as always there may be other local issues (landmarks or personal or factional conflicts) for adventurers to exploit.","fertility":320,"lvl":-300,"s":"swBd"},"a017170":{"xpos":17,"ypos":170,"k":"a017170","fertility":20,"lvl":-150,"s":"sNEwBd"},"a017171":{"xpos":17,"ypos":171,"k":"a017171","fertility":20,"lvl":0,"s":"sNEwBd"},"a017172":{"xpos":17,"ypos":172,"k":"a017172","tname":"Set's Vista","ttype":"gnoll","tale":"Set's Vista is another small gnoll encampment. It is more independent than Rampage Refuge. The setting is the old shoreline of the mid-earth sea. It is somewhat flat nearby but there are rises to the southwest and deeps to the northeast. In neither case is the transition extreme. As with many small gnoll camps, little is known about the particular local factions and goals.","fertility":320,"lvl":2,"s":"NEBd"},"a017173":{"xpos":17,"ypos":173,"k":"a017173","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":"wB"},"a017174":{"xpos":17,"ypos":174,"k":"a017174","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":"a"},"a017175":{"xpos":17,"ypos":175,"k":"a017175","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017176":{"xpos":17,"ypos":176,"k":"a017176","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017177":{"xpos":17,"ypos":177,"k":"a017177","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017178":{"xpos":17,"ypos":178,"k":"a017178","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017179":{"xpos":17,"ypos":179,"k":"a017179","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017180":{"xpos":17,"ypos":180,"k":"a017180","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017181":{"xpos":17,"ypos":181,"k":"a017181","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017182":{"xpos":17,"ypos":182,"k":"a017182","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017183":{"xpos":17,"ypos":183,"k":"a017183","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a017184":{"xpos":17,"ypos":184,"k":"a017184","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"SCD"},"a017185":{"xpos":17,"ypos":185,"k":"a017185","fertility":10,"lvl":0,"s":"SnabCD"},"a017186":{"xpos":17,"ypos":186,"k":"a017186","fertility":10,"lvl":-1,"s":"SnabCD"},"a017187":{"xpos":17,"ypos":187,"k":"a017187","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":"SnabCD"},"a017188":{"xpos":17,"ypos":188,"k":"a017188","fertility":10,"lvl":-300,"s":"SnabD"},"a017189":{"xpos":17,"ypos":189,"k":"a017189","fertility":20,"lvl":-450,"s":"sneabcd"},"a017190":{"xpos":17,"ypos":190,"k":"a017190","fertility":10,"lvl":-300,"s":"sNAc"},"a017191":{"xpos":17,"ypos":191,"k":"a017191","tname":"Quick Hold","ttype":"dwarf","tale":"Quick Hold is a QuickFoot clan settlement. This clan trains to move at human speed instead of dwarven. They are on the slopes of the Umurmur sea bed. They picked a spot rich in stone and metal resources. The only other population near them is a gnoll encampment of about the same size. There is an active rivalry between them. The dwarves try to trade with nearby populations or with Gyptia if they can. They search for more valuable resources, always in danger of \"digging too deep\". But mostly they enjoy their own craft and their own company. There is a landmark nearby which marks the spot where the settlement's founder is said to have won a race against a gnoll chief who wanted settle in the spot. This provides a focus for the settlement and its residents.","fertility":640,"lvl":-150,"s":"NWAB"},"a017192":{"xpos":17,"ypos":192,"k":"a017192","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":"Acd"},"a017193":{"xpos":17,"ypos":193,"k":"a017193","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":"ewcd"},"a017194":{"xpos":17,"ypos":194,"k":"a017194","fertility":10,"lvl":-150,"s":"sewabcd"},"a017195":{"xpos":17,"ypos":195,"k":"a017195","fertility":10,"lvl":-1,"s":"sNec"},"a017196":{"xpos":17,"ypos":196,"k":"a017196","fertility":40,"lvl":0,"s":"sNWA"},"a017197":{"xpos":17,"ypos":197,"k":"a017197","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"NEWABC"},"a017198":{"xpos":17,"ypos":198,"k":"a017198","fertilit