onship with the nearby gnoll village stable. However, for the most part this is a rest stop. Note that this is not the horde's favored type of terrain from before The Transit. It is very rough and steep terrain. However, in our era they have adapted to all terrain types.","fertility":320,"lvl":-150,"s":"sNEABd"},"a020173":{"xpos":20,"ypos":173,"k":"a020173","fertility":80,"lvl":0,"s":"sNEABd"},"a020174":{"xpos":20,"ypos":174,"k":"a020174","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"NEABCd"},"a020175":{"xpos":20,"ypos":175,"k":"a020175","tname":"Ax Craft","ttype":"human","tale":"Ax Craft (Netrit-Then)is a settlement spawned from the city of Gyptia. Their patron deity is Netrit-Then – An axe god. This is a group is favored by that the faction in Gyptia which is friendly with dwarves (Frábært ljós). This settlement was founded with that faction's help. It is a small group and trades with the great city mostly in fine weapons, especially axes. They make axes at half the price of normal craftspeople. They will also pay extra for any interesting or magical ax. There is also an extra chance that an ax crafted here will be of a quality so fine that it can be magically enhanced. It is said that, compared to other groups, Ax Craft dwarves are twice as good at creating magical axes. Anything that Frábært ljós favors is also likely to be well received in this settement and in some cases citizens of Netrit-Then may be used to implement some Frábært ljós plan.","fertility":320,"lvl":2,"s":"EwB"},"a020176":{"xpos":20,"ypos":176,"k":"a020176","fertility":40,"lvl":2,"s":"aB"},"a020177":{"xpos":20,"ypos":177,"k":"a020177","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":"c"},"a020178":{"xpos":20,"ypos":178,"k":"a020178","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"ec"},"a020179":{"xpos":20,"ypos":179,"k":"a020179","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"ebc"},"a020180":{"xpos":20,"ypos":180,"k":"a020180","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":"eb"},"a020181":{"xpos":20,"ypos":181,"k":"a020181","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"b"},"a020182":{"xpos":20,"ypos":182,"k":