fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027183":{"xpos":27,"ypos":183,"k":"a027183","fertility":80,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027184":{"xpos":27,"ypos":184,"k":"a027184","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027185":{"xpos":27,"ypos":185,"k":"a027185","tname":"Uncanny Terror","ttype":"gnoll","tale":"Uncanny Terror is a gnoll settlement that is dedicated to Kek/Kauket. This deity can appear either in male or female form. Kek is the male form. The deity's female form is known as Kauket. This \"pair\" is/are the god/goddess of Chaos and Darkness, as well as being the concept of primordial darkness. The gnolls also, as always, worship Set. While Kek is not evil (not dedicated to destruction) it is a deity that inspires terror because it is so strange and unsettling.\r\nThere are some settlements that are within reach of this gnollish source of unease and the gnolls are happy to make them uneasy. Though they are powerful this group is more dedicated to momentary chaos than permanent overthrow of the existing order. If they could increase their power they might become more ambitious. Therefore, they are looking for such opportunities. Is there, perhaps, a nearby shrine to the cobra god that may contain artifacts that would serve that purpose? It is rumred that there is.","fertility":2560,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027186":{"xpos":27,"ypos":186,"k":"a027186","fertility":20,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027187":{"xpos":27,"ypos":187,"k":"a027187","fertility":80,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027188":{"xpos":27,"ypos":188,"k":"a027188","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"SCD"},"a027189":{"xpos":27,"ypos":189,"k":"a027189","fertility":20,"lvl":0,"s":"nab"},"a027190":{"xpos":27,"ypos":190,"k":"a027190","fertility":10,"lvl":0,"s":"scd"},"a027191":{"xpos":27,"ypos":191,"k":"a027191","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"NAB"},"a027192":{"xpos":27,"ypos":192,"k":"a027192","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":""},"a027193":{"xpos":27,"ypos":193,"k":"a027193","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"c"},"a027194":{"xpos":27,"ypos":194,"k":"a027194","fertility":10,"lvl":2,"s":"